---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About OpsBash — Free DevOps Tools for Engineers"
  description="OpsBash builds free, browser-based tools for DevOps engineers who work with Linux, AWS, Kubernetes and CI/CD pipelines. No accounts, no paywalls, no fluff."
  canonicalURL="https://opsbash.com/about"
>
<main class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">

  <div class="mb-10">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-3" style="color: #34d399;">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4" style="color: var(--fg);">About OpsBash</h1>
    <p class="text-base leading-relaxed max-w-xl" style="color: var(--fg2);">
      Professional tools for engineers who live in terminals, write Kubernetes manifests, and debug cron jobs at 2 AM.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-5">

    <div class="rounded-2xl p-6" style="background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-3" style="color: var(--fg);">The story</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3 text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--fg2);">
        <p>
          OpsBash started from a simple frustration: most online DevOps tools are either covered in ads, locked behind accounts, or just wrong. A cron expression validator that doesn't understand AWS EventBridge syntax. A base64 encoder that sends your data to a server. A "free" tool that's free for three uses.
        </p>
        <p>
          DevOps engineers work with Linux schedulers, AWS CloudWatch Events, Kubernetes CronJobs, and GitHub Actions pipelines — sometimes all on the same day. Each platform has its own cron dialect, its own quirks, its own edge cases. You shouldn't have to look that up from a 10-year-old Stack Overflow answer.
        </p>
        <p>
          OpsBash is built to fix that. Every tool is purpose-built for the specific needs of operations engineers: accurate, fast, private, and completely free.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl p-6" style="background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--fg);">Our mission</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          <span class="w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5"
                style="background: #0f2415; border: 1px solid #1a3a22;">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3" style="color: #34d399;" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </span>
          <span><strong style="color: var(--fg);">Solve real daily problems.</strong> Every tool exists because a real DevOps engineer ran into a real problem. Not because it fills a feature matrix.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          <span class="w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5"
                style="background: #0f2415; border: 1px solid #1a3a22;">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3" style="color: #34d399;" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </span>
          <span><strong style="color: var(--fg);">Be accurate, not just functional.</strong> The cron builder correctly handles Linux/Unix, AWS EventBridge (6-field format with <code class="text-xs px-1 py-0.5 rounded font-mono" style="background: var(--code-bg);">?</code> wildcard), GitHub Actions UTC scheduling, and Kubernetes CronJob manifests — with the actual syntax differences between them, not a one-size-fits-all approximation.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          <span class="w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5"
                style="background: #0f2415; border: 1px solid #1a3a22;">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3" style="color: #34d399;" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </span>
          <span><strong style="color: var(--fg);">Keep it private.</strong> Every tool runs entirely in your browser. No cron expressions, no configuration data, no user input of any kind is transmitted to our servers.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          <span class="w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5"
                style="background: #0f2415; border: 1px solid #1a3a22;">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3" style="color: #34d399;" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </span>
          <span><strong style="color: var(--fg);">Stay free.</strong> No accounts. No pricing tiers. No "basic" vs "pro" split that puts the features you actually need behind a paywall.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          <span class="w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 mt-0.5"
                style="background: #0f2415; border: 1px solid #1a3a22;">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3" style="color: #34d399;" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
          </span>
          <span><strong style="color: var(--fg);">No fluff.</strong> No hero videos, no testimonial carousels, no cookie-consent pop-ups covering the tool you came to use. Just the tool.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl p-6" style="background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--fg);">What we build for</h2>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--fg2);">
        OpsBash tools are designed around the real workflow of platform and operations engineers:
      </p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-sm" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full shrink-0" style="background: #34d399;"></span>
          Linux / Unix crontab scheduling
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-sm" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full shrink-0" style="background: #34d399;"></span>
          AWS EventBridge &amp; CloudWatch Events
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-sm" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full shrink-0" style="background: #34d399;"></span>
          Kubernetes CronJob manifests
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-sm" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full shrink-0" style="background: #34d399;"></span>
          GitHub Actions scheduled workflows
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-sm" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full shrink-0" style="background: #34d399;"></span>
          CI/CD pipelines &amp; automation
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-sm" style="color: var(--fg2);">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full shrink-0" style="background: #34d399;"></span>
          General sysadmin &amp; scripting tasks
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl p-6" style="background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-4" style="color: var(--fg);">Tools available now</h2>
      <a href="/cron-builder" class="flex items-start gap-4 group" style="text-decoration: none;">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 transition-colors"
             style="background: #0f2415; border: 1px solid #1a3a22;">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" style="color: #34d399;" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium mb-1" style="color: var(--fg);">Cron Expression Generator</p>
          <p class="text-xs leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--fg2);">Generate and validate cron expressions with visual dropdowns. Get plain-English explanations, next 10 run times in your local timezone, and ready-to-use output for Linux, AWS CloudWatch, GitHub Actions, and Kubernetes.</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-xs font-medium" style="color: #34d399;">Try the tool →</p>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl p-6" style="background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border);">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-3" style="color: var(--fg);">Get in touch</h2>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--fg2);">
        Found a bug? Have a tool request? Spotted an edge case we handle wrong?
        <a href="/contact" class="hover:underline ml-1 font-medium" style="color: #34d399;">Reach out →</a>
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mt-2" style="color: var(--fg2);">
        We respond within 48 hours at <a href="mailto:contact@opsbash.com" class="hover:underline font-mono" style="color: #34d399;">contact@opsbash.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</main>
</Layout>
